caption: Excellent service with a very fun and inviting staff. I ordered the conchita pibil, which is one of my favorite dishes, and this place exceeded all expectations. Habanero sauce was incredibly flavorful but not overly spicy and had enough balance to where someone with a low spice tolerance would still probably like it.  Overall 10/10 will definitely be back.
The food is so tasty and the best customer service, was a wonderful experience...

We arrived at a little past 4, they were not open on time, we waited 10 minutes, called them, waited for response,  none received. We left and saw 3 more people attempting to get in. They also walked away.  Take note that 4:00 opening time, is not reliable. Call way ahead of time to insure that they are open.
Might be biased, since this restaurant is at the end of our block, but this is some of the best Mexican food we've ever had. Eating from here is always a treat.
The best place ❤ green mole its fantastic
Can't wait to dine in. The food was terrific, the Moles Manchamanteles was sublime. the portions are generous, and the sides (we had the fresh guacamole) were tangy and delicious.
Went to mis moles to celebrate my husbands birthday we loved everything about it. Food, atmosphere and especially the service. Will definitely go back.

The food here is amazing. We had the chicken and waffles and shrimp and grits. I loved that they had options for non pork eaters, and their extensive tea selection. Great service, looking forward to coming back and trying their other menu items.

The pictures don’t do this place justice. It’s amazing! The churros are the best I’ve had. Also ordered the Mole Menchamental Lamb, the vegetarian enchiladas, and the passion fruit mezcal margaritas. All SO good...like my mama was cooking for me. Also the owner Gino is amazing!!

I would recommend this restaurant to anyone looking for quality Mexican food that brings a unique taste, separating it from your average restaurant.  The general manager is extremely friendly and accommodating and the staff of equal stature.  The food is excellent, my girlfriend and I had no complaints. In all honesty, one of the best corn tamales I have ever had was provided as an appetizer.  As an entree, I ordered the duck breast with one of their four specialty sauces the chef makes daily, and I can not wait to return to try the other three.  For anyone reading this, I strongly encourage you to give this restaurant a try.

I've never met a more welcoming manager than Branko at Mis Moles. Really a special and unique experience that made the excellent food by chef Geno Bahena that much better. I had the mole manchamanteles con pollo, sopes for an appetizer, and the tamal de chocolate for dessert. Everything was perfect (especially the dessert omg if you love chocolate you have to get it 😭). Satisfyingly taditional but with creative spins that make it worth the trip to taste. Great wine selection and strong turkish coffee to go with it too! 👌🏼

Date night at Mis Moles did not disappoint! Branko, Amber, and their staff were extremely welcoming and very attentive. I absolutely loved that the food tasted homemade because the hispanic in me was craving it for a while!  They were also covid friendly. Very minimal seating, mostly pick up only for food available, everyone was in masks, and it looked all super sanitized!  Thank you for a great experience at this gem in North Chicago. I’ll definitely be coming back!

Mis Moles has super delicious and creative Mexican food for meat eaters and vegetarians alike. If you like spicy their salsa habanera is out of this world and a must try. The team at Mis Moles are always a pleasure to interact with. A very nice complement to their fantastic food!

We are HUGE fans of both the food and staff at Mis Moles. The food is made with such care and every interaction with staff has only been generous. At this point, we’ve ordered almost everything off the menu and each meal has been phenomenal — even when delivered.

Everything about this restaurant is amazing! The menu is diverse and interesting, the service was extremely nice and helpful, and the food was just incredible. I’m planning on getting food from here much more often and you should too.
Beautifull place!
This place is the best! The moles are amazing and the sopa azteca is a must on cold nights!

We ordered curbside pickup and it was easy to pull up and receive our order - a mole poblano rojo con pollo and a Carne Asada. Everything was delicious - the mole was wonderful and not overly hot/spicy, the chicken tender and tasty with a light dusting of sesame seeds, and even the tortillas were great quality and I imagine made from scratch. I ate some of the mole straight wrapped up in a tortilla and enjoyed that decision as well. The carne asada was tender and juicy, and the guacomole fresh and tasty. Even the garnish in the mole (I think a couple slices of zuchini) was tasty, as if the chef was determined that everything should have a distinct and enjoyable flavor. We plan to be return customers.
When you don't want to cook, please support local restaurants struggling during this pandemic.  Delicious food, friendly service.
Delish! Loved everything

Food, service, people - all 100%! We’ve tried majority of the apps and enjoyed them all - Don’t skip the soup or the taquitos! Marg is a must go. This last round we had the house favorite carne asada, which was delicious. Loved the plantains that came with it. This restaurant has been added to our hidden gem favorites!

A jewel! The food is delicious (& great quality), the place is beautiful, and the people are friendly. This restaurant features Mexican food from various regions. It reminds me of some restaurants I’d visit in Mexico City, where I’d find flavors from all over Mexico. We’ve tried a few of their dishes and can’t wait to try more!
The ceviche as well as the mole dish we tried were great.

We had a great experience. The food was delicious. We had their famous mole dishes, margaritas and flan. The server was so nice and they all made us feel like family. Will definitely be going back often.
This was a fantastic restaurant as Little Bucharest, and it's a fantastic restaurant as Mis Moles - high quality food, excellent portions, and exceptional service. Super grateful to live nearby!
The best Mexican food I've had in Chicago. More refined than your average taqueria but also so much more delicious

The food was not only exquisite but the presentation was extremely artful 👌🏽 I also have to give it up to the staff who made our first date so warm and inviting to the last bite. Bravo to the Chef, brava to the hard working ladies in the background. Highly recommended! 😋
The food is so delicious! Best mole enchiladas I’ve had. The GM has amazing hospitality, makes you feel like home. I will definitely come back and I highly recommend!
Un manjar of the gods...enjoyed a delicious dinner with my husband. Local restaurant with authentic Mexican cuisine. Head to Mis Moles and expand your food palate.

First time there and meeting the owner, very friendly, food was tasty and a lot of variety, they were doing the best to accommodate our taste and preference in food. Definitely going back, it was a pleasure being there. Thank you for making us feel welcomed!!!
Rare to find really good mole around the city and this didn't disappoint! 😄 the service and hospitality sets mis moles apart too! I'll be back to bring other friends and family!
Love this place! Just tried it for the first time and the food was fantastic. The owner even served us. Highly recommend ❤️❤️❤️. Will be back

WOW. Im beating myself up for not having come sooner. Came down Elston for a nice Mexican Independence Day dinner after months of pledging to visit and I am mourning the meals I missed. It's such a charming atmosphere (not tacky), memorable songs playing (not overplayed), and super attentive staff (not smothering) - Three things other restaurants tend to overdo. I'll definitely be back for more (and more take-out.)

Excellent restaurant. I had lamb and my mole was exquisite. It was a fun atmosphere and we got to talk with the head chef. He paid close attention to every table and made sure they were enjoying their meal. Everything was clean and comfortable, I’d recommend getting dessert. We got the churros dipped in hot chocolate sauce and I want to go back just thinking about it.
Delicious food and very welcoming knowledge staff. A hidden gem. 10/10 will go again

Amazing food and drinks. Lucky to have such a wonderful gem of a restaurant in the neighborhood. I had never had mole before and now will making this a regular date night spot! The food is amazing, drinks are strong, and the patio is spacious.

Absolutely amazing experience. The homemade tortillas, great entrees with amazing amounts of seafood, and great drinks were so filling and delicious. The service and atmosphere was fantastic and welcoming. Highly recommend and will be back soon!

Came here for dinner and it was amazing. My boyfriend got a mojito and I got a passion fruit margarita, we split the queso and each got a seafood dish.  Staff and as so friendly and helpful without feeling like they're on top of you.  Can't wait to come back and try more food!

Ms. Mole's is a hidden gem on Northside of Chicago! Had an excellent dinner there tonight. The food was wonderful, but also beautiful! We started with Guacamole and Ceviche, both were amazing. We had a party of 5 people, we were able to sit outside and social distance comfortably. The restaurant took every precaution to make sure everything was served with our safety and comfort in mind. Each person in our party ordered something different. Each plate had different elements of flavors that went so well together. We had the Arroz a la Tumbada, Callos de Hacha en Pipián, Special Thursday Mole with Duck, Enchiladas Vegetarianas, and Atun a La Mexicana. For dessert, we each had an item and again, each dish had such flavorful elements. I think my ultimate favorites were the Chocolate Tamale and the Churros. Thank you, Chef Gino Bahena and Branko for making our evening wonderful! We definitely plan on going back soon. I’m also hoping to take a Taste of Mexico cooking class with Chef Gino sometime soon.

They are know for their mole. Get the mole. Enjoy the mole! Verde is my favorite. Also their vagetarian enchiladas in a tomatillo sauce are amazing. To note they do have Pacofico in bottles, not on the menu.

Best Mole in Chicago hands down! Chef Geno is an absolute genius and the staff is top notch. The Margaritas are to die for and everything that they serve will have you coming back for more. I have definitely found my new favorite spot!

Hmm... where do I start.. I’m first generation American to Mexican born parents. I have grown up with mole only on special occasions. This mole tastes like a combination of all of my mom’s/grandmother’s best mole put together. The Nopales with mariscos was exquisite as well. The cherry on top was the fresh hand made tortillas they give you. (You can always order more as you go). If I show you what my napkin looks like you would know that this mole was just right. Try them out, I promise you will not regret.

I really wish i had tried the food, but unfortunately i couldn't because its the second time i go by and the restaurant is closed before the time on the door. very disappointed. i got there at 7 on a Sunday and the waitress said the kitchen was closed which is why I am giving it a 1 star review, as i'm sure the food is delicious but their hours and times are just very unorganized. made me waste my time not once but twice!

We were impressed by the quality and selection of moles, homemade tortillas, and unique options. We sat outside under grapevines and twinkle lights. The area was nice and shady at 6pm. We were happy to see the restaurant doing a good job with spacing and mask wearing. Check out any menu options with mole and don’t miss the churros. The staff were warm and welcoming. Def recommend making a reservation. Looking forward to returning to this neighborhood gem!
Amazing food. Everyone is extremely friendly. I am definitely coming back.

The chef is amazing and the moles are wonderful. They have a their full menu, but they are not actually running the daily specials yet. I recommend you ask for a small sample of the moles they do have before you decide. They are all pretty amazing, but so very different from each other.

The staff was friendly and inviting. We were greeted out front by the owner who sat us personally at our socially distanced table. The menu has so many great options we wanted to try them all. The waitress Cindy was kind enough to bring us a sampler of some of their different moles. Best mole I’ve had, hands down.
The staff was amazing. The food is super delicious. The owner treated us like family. Coming back real soon
Amazing place!!
Really lovely!! Food was amazing and the atmosphere friendly and fun.  A great addition to the neighborhood!!

Amazing service and food! Staff members and the owner were hospitable and accommodating. We enjoyed a lovely bottle of Romanian Merlot. As an app we enjoyed Sopes Surtidos "Xilonen" and for dinner we had Callos de Hacha en Pipian and Nopales Asados con Mariscos Al Chipotle.  What I found so memorable about the place was the owners warmth! I was so amused by his Romanian "holy water" which definitely wasn't what I expected  but was pleasantly surprised! If he happens to bring it around, do yourself a favor and give it a whirl.  Happy to have visited this little neighborhood gem 🤗 will be making this my go to spot!

This is my new favorite restaurant. I highly recommend the Thursday special, green mole. I tried it with the fish option and it was seriously, seriously delicious. Fish was served rare and to absolute perfection. For an appetizer we tried the guacamole, which I am sad to say might actually be better than my own, and that is a really difficult thing for me to admit since I am known as the guac master among my friends and family. So yes. The food is super good. Also, friendly staff who take care in social distancing and corona virus precautions. Also, nice beer, wine, and cocktail menu!! Vegetarian and pescatarian friendly. House made tortillas were excellent. Definitely will be back soon!!

This place is great. The staff could not be more friendly, professional and hospitable.  The side patio is quiet and away from the main street. And the food is amazing. I loved the seafood nopales dish with cactus leaves. Huge portion; perfectly seasoned.  Our new favorite Mexican place.
Everything we had was so rich and flavorful! Can’t go wrong with their food, but I highly recommend the  Callos de Hacha en Pipián. Some of the best scallops I’ve ever had. Will be back soon!
This is an incredible experience. The food is outstanding and the staff very knowledgeable. Your arrival and entry into this food paradise is unforgettable.

What a wonderful addition to the neighborhood. We each had the tasting menu with a wine pairing to share. It began with an appetizer of two very different, yet equally amazing sopes and a flauta. The soup was beyond flavorful with a fish and meat course that included different dishes for each of us and delicious homemade tortillas. We were blown away by the flavors in each dish that were so unique and clearly made with love and care. The waiter, Jose, was friendly and knowledgeable yet gave us space on our date night and it was nice that the chef stopped by to chat and share his experiences. We hope that he is able to publish his cookbook so that we can try to replicate at home. Until then we are going to look into the cooking classes to take our friends for an adventure. Try Mis Moles, recommend the tasting menu with wine, but from looking around there didn’t seem to be a disappointed table. Great outside seating and plenty of free street parking. What a gem.
Took my mom here for her b day. She loved it. Drinks and food were excellent and the owner was very friendly and inviting. Will def be back soon.

Great new spot in the neighborhood. They had a black, red and green mole they let us sample and all were great. Got the lamb with mole and wanted to lick the plate. The churros were great and the chocolate tamale was a decadent surprise. Nice patio.
Best spot for mole in the city. My husband says it’s better than his abuelita’s (shhh!). And the homemade tortillas are amazing. We’ll be back many times.
My husband and I have been here twice since moving to Albany park in June, the food is delicious, the servers are attentive, highly recommend the ceviche, margaritas, sopes, churros, everything!
Excellent quality and good food (Romanian and Mexican )
I’ve just had dinner with my family here. It was a perfect experience: excellent food, great service. “Carne asada” (charcoal grilled beef) was to die for. I strongly recommend this restaurant!
Absolutely perfect. Fresh ingredients. Great presentation. Flawless service. We will definitely be back.
Wonderful passion fruit margaritas. Dinner was delicious. The service was very pleasant and welcome. Oh so good!
Amazing food and service! Each mole is unique in its own and Chef Geno puts his heart in everything he makes! Would recommend this spot to anyone, don’t miss out!

I absolutely love this place! Went twice last week and everything I had both times was delicious. I’m a foodie and I’m so glad this opened up in my neighborhood. I had their taquitos, queso con chorizo with homemade tortillas 😋 nopales asados con mariscos, scallops dish and arroz con mariscos wow that was my ultimate favorite!! Oh and let’s not forget the churros con chocolate and ice cream. This is my new favorite restaurant in Chicago! I’ll be there again this week :)
The steak dinner was delicious! Passion fruit margaritas were refreshing! The staff was great. The girls had a lovely evening! Thankyou
Food is absolutely delicious and it’s met with excellent service.. Highly recommend
Great food great people. Glad they opened shop
Excellent moles as the name implies!  Nice menu.  Great passion fruit margaritas.

Among the best moles I’ve had in the US. A lifelong Mexico City resident, so I know my moles. Had the duck with red mole, which I didn’t leave a trace of on the plate. And the nopales asados with mariscos in chipotle is mind-bogglingly good. Highly recommend this place. Great, friendly service as well.
Great Food, Great Service, Outdoor Seating, No Delivery yet but they are working on it. Great Place! Welcome to the neighborhood.

Highly recommend this new gem on Elston just north of Addison. We absolutely loved the every bite from chef Geno Bahena's kitchen. If you were around Logan Square in the late 90's, you may recall Geno's Ixcapuzalco restaurant on Milwaukee. His moles are incredible. Can't say enough about the friendliness of the attentive staff. What a welcome addition to the neighborhood!

Mia Moles Restaurant was so worth the wait a beautiful way to enjoy my birthday with phenomenal and respectful staff. Delicious food tasty salsa’s and the pomegranate and passion fruit margarita was so very good! Just made our next reservation for Saturday night to come back and enjoy the delicious food and drinks!
